{"id": "1413885613500924007", "channel_id": "1413885613500924007", "type": 0, "author_id": "302718766289256448", "author_name": "zekiei", "author_bot": false, "content": "This is just an example, but even when painted, some cards still show information on their effects. Here included are Solareflare explaining Hyperfare and Kath's 2-cost explaining str gain. \nFor reference I got to this using GRamona's 2-cost, during the last battle in Horla's rerun event", "timestamp": "2025-09-06T13:56:38.983000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1413885613781946468", "filename": "Screenshot_2025-09-02-21-05-44-770_com.qookkagames.z1.gp.hk.jpg", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 196706, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1413885613500924007/1413885613781946468/Screenshot_2025-09-02-21-05-44-770_com.qookkagames.z1.gp.hk.jpg?ex=69ff3d17&is=69fdeb97&hm=b17e3282be8b932002062a645c8e9baf8986fdaa78079f168f8ef84c705a4ef6&"}, {"id": "1413885614192853124", "filename": "Screenshot_2025-09-02-21-05-51-642_com.qookkagames.z1.gp.hk.jpg", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 197195, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1413885613500924007/1413885614192853124/Screenshot_2025-09-02-21-05-51-642_com.qookkagames.z1.gp.hk.jpg?ex=69ff3d17&is=69fdeb97&hm=03648d5216b706bb06287baa65a877843c757b2fa0ce9c4657a228bcfac17ae1&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1413885613500924007", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "💭「Processing」Paint effect shows a little too much infos", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
{"id": "1413879835658424462", "channel_id": "1413879835658424462", "type": 0, "author_id": "233874560682950656", "author_name": "wolfierce", "author_bot": false, "content": "Hello,\n\nSo I report it as a bug but it may be an intended behavior:\nUsing a copying Posse like \"The Lone Seed\" on Tawil's command card \"Omniscient Verity\" leads to copying the card it is copying, instead of duplicating \"Omniscient Verity\".\n\nI must say this is a risky way to code the card, because I'd interpret that \"Omniscient Verity\" is literally just a pointer, and that most likely would lead to headaches to solve eventual issues.\n\nI'd advice to make Tawil's card copy paste effects bluntly. But then again, it depends on how the game is structured, so it might be tricky to do this and I'm making a bit wild guess.", "timestamp": "2025-09-06T13:33:41.438000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1413879837499588730", "filename": "2025-09-06_15-26-58.mp4", "content_type": "video/mp4", "size": 18791342, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1413879835658424462/1413879837499588730/2025-09-06_15-26-58.mp4?ex=69ff37b5&is=69fde635&hm=268607be4d08d1e4cf26029cb6153d2e7ff07884fbb21773ccc3a09617dc5cd4&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1413879835658424462", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Tawil Omniscient Verity unexpected copy behaviour", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
